# Licence

## Default — CC BY 4.0

Copyright © Felix Sargent and contributors.

Except where stated otherwise below, the original contents of this
repository — site code, ETL pipeline, generated tables, charts, prose,
SVG and PNG outputs — are licensed under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International licence:

> https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

You may share and adapt the work for any purpose, including
commercially, provided you give appropriate credit, link to the
licence, and indicate if changes were made. Suggested attribution:

> "electionresults.uk by Felix Sargent (https://electionresults.uk),
> licensed under CC BY 4.0."

Note that Creative Commons does not recommend CC licences for
software in general. The choice is deliberate here: this repository
publishes a single static analysis site, the code and the derived
data are intended to be reused under one consistent attribution
regime, and the patent / source-distribution concerns CC licences
don't address don't apply to a prerendered web project.

## Carve-out — LEAP-derived data: CC BY-SA 4.0

The CSV files under `docs/leap/` are republished from Andrew Teale's
Local Elections Archive Project (https://www.andrewteale.me.uk/leap/)
under their original CC BY-SA 3.0 / GFDL terms. Any dataset
**derived** from these files — including aggregated tables, joined
extracts, and downloads on the site that incorporate LEAP rows — is
released under the one-way-compatible upgrade:

> Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International
> https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

with attribution to Andrew Teale and a link back to the LEAP archive.

The share-alike obligation rides on the **data**, not on the analysis
code or the editorial prose around it. Code, charts, and pages
remain CC BY 4.0 even when they describe LEAP-derived figures.

## Upstream third-party data

The following materials in `docs/` are reproduced under their
upstream licences and are not relicensed by this repository:

- House of Commons Library Local Election Handbooks
  (`docs/LEH-*.xlsx`, `docs/local_elections_*.xlsx`,
  `docs/local-elections-*.xlsx`, `docs/CBP*.xlsx`,
  `docs/data_tables.xlsx`) — Open Parliament Licence v3.0
  (https://www.parliament.uk/site-information/copyright-parliament/open-parliament-licence/)
- Democracy Club candidate / results exports
  (`docs/dc-candidates-*.csv`, `docs/downloaded-*.csv`) — CC BY 4.0
  (https://democracyclub.org.uk/copyright/)
- Open Council Data UK rolls and history
  (`docs/opencouncildata_*.csv`, `docs/history*.csv`) — CC BY-SA 4.0
  (https://opencouncildata.co.uk/)
- IndyLive Radio 2022 Scottish STV CSV
  (`docs/scotland-2022-stv-indylive.csv`) — CC BY-SA 4.0
- LEAP — Andrew Teale (`docs/leap/**`) — CC BY-SA 3.0 / GFDL,
  see `docs/leap-source.md`

In every case the files are reproduced for analytical use under the
upstream licence; consult the upstream source for refresh, errata,
and re-use beyond what those licences permit.
